Get info
- gem info gem_name

Contents of the gem
- gem contents gem_name

Unpack gem
- gem unpack gem_name # => current_folder
Or You can also specify the folder
- gem unpack gem_name --target=~/target_folder

Alternative:
- bundle info gem_name
- bundle info --path gem_name
- bundle show gem_name

Or just open the gem's folder
- gem open gem_name
or
- bundle open gem_name

redo changes if you `gem open gem_name`
- gem pristine gem_name
or
- bundle pristine

The `bundle pristine` command will restore ALL installed gems for a particular bundle to their original state.

within ruby:
- Gem.find_files('colorize')

source:
  - https://batsov.com/articles/2020/12/16/inspecting-the-contents-of-a-ruby-gem/
